[[File:WotanWeave.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Basic Corkscrew Avoid]]
The '''Corkscrew Avoid''' was a spiral or corkscrew maneuver used by [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] to evade enemy fire while maintaining a particular heading. Some [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] veterans called the maneuver the '''Wotan Weave'''<ref name="TIE Fighter: The Official Strategy Guide">''[[TIE Fighter: The Official Strategy Guide]]''</ref> after its developer, [[Wotan]], though this name was more frequently used by [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] pilots.<ref name="X-Wing: The Official Strategy Guide">''[[X-Wing: The Official Strategy Guide]]''</ref> [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] used a variation of this tactic to enable him to launch proton torpedoes against capital ships while presenting a near-impossible target for the ship's gunners.<ref name="X-Wing: The Bacta War">''[[X-Wing: The Bacta War]]''</ref>

